# My everyday loaf based on morph

starter:
  rye
  water
  hydration = 80%

leaven ^ 10%:
  starter
  rye = 4 * starter
  water
  hydration = 100%

grain:
  prairie_gold
  hard_red = prairie_gold
  spelt = 5%
  barley = 5%
  buckwheat = 5%

dry:
  grain
  vwg = 3%
  potato_flakes = 3%
  flaxseed_meal = 5%
  yeast = 0.5%
  salt = 1.8%

wet:
  water
  ascorbic_acid_1p = 50ppm * 100 * grain.total
  leaven = 30%
  olive_oil = 5%
  honey = 5%
  yogurt = 5%

dough:
  wet
  dry
  hydration = 70%
  # 200g/L of flour
  # total_flour = 660g # 13 inch
  total_flour = 460g # 9 inch

/*
April 18, 2026

Changes

Zoji pan weighs 773g. KA pan weighs 725g.

Starter is 5 days old.

Mixed the leaven with 70F water about 20:20 left at 60F overnight.
Initial leaven temperature is ?F. RT is 75F.

Leaven pH = 4.13 at 8:00. At 275mL. I should have used cold water.

I started about 7:45

Dry is 83F. Wet is 54F. Mix is 65F.

Used the KA for mixing. Mixed about 8:20. Stopped after 3 minutes.
DT after mixing is 68F. RT is 73F. 

30 minute rest in fridge. After rest the dough is 59F.

Kneaded 8 minutes in KA. 8:55

DT at end of kneading is 68F. Into the cambro for 30 minutes in the
fridge. S&F, back to the fridge.

Shaped at 10:30 and into the pan. Proof at 76F.

I added 120mL of water to the pan at the beginning of preheat. It
lasted 12 minutes into the bake.

Baked at 14:22 for 40 minutes at 350F. It was about 1 inch above top
of pan.

Close to perfect appearance. Good flavor.

*/


